laboratory_examinations.findings: Closure of the neovascular membrane, no evident subretinal fluid was seen.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Three weeks after treatment visual acuity improved from 20/60 to 20/40. Nine weeks later, visual acuity decreased to 20/50, with a small area of shallow subretinal fluid observed. Thirty-four weeks after PDT, visual acuity was 20/60, subretinal fluid resolved, and fluorescein angiography showed no further changes.

laboratory_examinations.findings: A well-defined classic choroidal neovascular membrane was detected.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Two months later, clinical evidence of subretinal fluid was detected.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Positive for a defect in chromosome 2p16-21 characteristic of malattia leventinese.
